<subSubSection id="36C5CA0AA458B2A7414A8850D57C15C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FE7F3B42A9054ADD0BFF0689FC960B24" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F4B6014E406167EC8EEE18E40F875A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
One new species was described (
<bibRefCitation id="31EEF56FF990ED829FEEC821B7D31347" author="Han, H-X." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="885 - 922" refId="B5535839" refString="Han, H-X., Galsworthy, A. C., Xue, D-Y., 2009. A survey of the genus Geometra Linnaeus (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae). Journal of Natural History 43: 885 - 922" title="A survey of the genus Geometra Linnaeus (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae)" volume="43" year="2009">Han et al. 2009b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="AC639B8F521B31C19ECFBBD88258535E" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" genus="Loxochila" lsidName="Loxochila" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9624666F8DBC040A74435A333F55FF82" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Loxochila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CD914F436CC433A77AC48F26C42105DF" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Geometra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Geometra" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B05A648F5E6D79F469E0559EFC0041" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Geometra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="0FBEAC412A72B3F3DCE39067E232C6A0" author="Parsons, MS" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO, Clayton North, Victoria, Australia" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5536979" refString="Parsons, MS, Scoble, MJ, Honey, MR, Pitkin, LM, Pitkin, BR, 1999. Geometrid moths of the world: a catalogue (Lepidoptera, Geometridae). CSIRO, Clayton North, Victoria, Australia" title="Geometrid moths of the world: a catalogue (Lepidoptera, Geometridae)." year="1999">Parsons et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="E6DFBE1A9A3166AC3FF71D5C31285133" author="Rajaei, Hossein" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5537022" refString="ScobleMHausmannAOnline list of valid and available names of the Geometridae of the Worldhttp://www.lepbarcoding.org/geometridae/species_checklists.php2019-11-01T00:00:00+02:00" year="2015">Scoble and Hausmann (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="59D5259190C5D300560FA89272B16238" author="Han, H-X." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="885 - 922" refId="B5535839" refString="Han, H-X., Galsworthy, A. C., Xue, D-Y., 2009. A survey of the genus Geometra Linnaeus (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae). Journal of Natural History 43: 885 - 922" title="A survey of the genus Geometra Linnaeus (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae)" volume="43" year="2009">Han et al. (2009b)</bibRefCitation>
retained this classification in their revision of 
<taxonomicName id="6D811D454BF0C3F50C54BFEDD00D09D4" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Geometra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Geometra" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="80E7872B14144A10391E2F59F3016D82" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Geometra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which divided the genus into two species groups. The type species of 
<taxonomicName id="E0C9FFDCFE0A30AB6138C78165B0A436" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" genus="Loxochila" lsidName="Loxochila" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E4A7FB127B2A14F10B17F21788828E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Loxochila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, at the time named 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1595959F99DBB6CEA9A92F7AA339" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Geometra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Geometra smaragdus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdus">
<emphasis id="6B70CF590BD39D1B8868DBB2CAFD3933" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Geometra smaragdus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Butler), served as the eponymous taxon of the 
<emphasis id="16E27CF561E2A7DD3FBC15E34FB35293" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">smaragdus</emphasis>
species group. The molecular phylogeny of 
<bibRefCitation id="FA28DA0FB5443755DF78A116A4522E6E" author="Ban, Xiaoshung" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="653 - 672" refId="B5534990" refString="Ban, Xiaoshung, Jiang, Nan, Cheng, Rui, Xue, Dayong, Han, Hongxiang, 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184: 653 - 672" title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions." volume="184" year="2018">Ban et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
demonstrated that the 
<emphasis id="F721B56C348EBD50D30758845AB82D44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">smaragdus</emphasis>
group is a strongly-supported clade that also contains one species from a different genus (
<taxonomicName id="D4C63A9048F7901CC62A74FD8B487D00" authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Tanaorhinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tanaorhinus kina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kina">
<emphasis id="156DB0C15885FBB2834406874061C764" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Tanaorhinus kina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Swinhoe). 
<bibRefCitation id="5EB7A2E72439AE6E11BA5A78EECA3EFE" author="Ban, Xiaoshung" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="653 - 672" refId="B5534990" refString="Ban, Xiaoshung, Jiang, Nan, Cheng, Rui, Xue, Dayong, Han, Hongxiang, 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184: 653 - 672" title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions." volume="184" year="2018">Ban et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
consequently re-instated the generic status of 
<taxonomicName id="79A4F340A7D2D007FA3D4736F07D2CFB" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" genus="Loxochila" lsidName="Loxochila" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="30806EAC33A3476D121F3668E2CD9A9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Loxochila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and transferred the species in the 
<emphasis id="9C5B5E57E0C6D600273F195774E5B2B1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">smaragdus</emphasis>
group, including 
<taxonomicName id="FEA52DA283EE81DC92F9EB66B9E3DB43" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="T." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="T. kina" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="kina">
<emphasis id="DC1B1F4362E8424DAF3FE3EB856E2D76" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">T. kina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to this genus.
</paragraph>
